This paper deals with natural language inference (NLI) and machine learning techniques to address biases in NLI datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses adversarial learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses deep learning models, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions image captioning, which is related to computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for adversarial attacks, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
